ght direction. 35 minutes hiking through thinning trees to the open. Continue straight up the slope toward the Norhteast summit in 20 minutes. The northwest summit is slightly lower. Views are of Kootenay Lake, the ferry, Crawford Bay and countless peaks.<br \/>\nSouth Summit(s). Following sparse flagging heading southwest from the parking area. Head up the road cut-bank, turn left, pass an old A-frame cabin\/shelter, cross two gullies and head to the left of a white rock talus slope in forest.\u00a0 Climb the second rock slide to the ridge above and the first summit.\u00a0 The second summit is a 90 meter (290 ft)\u00a0 decent then up the alpine ridge<\/h4>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/section>\n<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Two scrambles right at the pass, the watershed of the Purcell Range between the mid point of Kootenay Lake and Kimberly. Difficulty: B2 &#8211; moderate scramble Elevation Gain: 242m Key Elevations: Parking area &#8220;the pass&#8221;: 6450&#8242;, Sphinx 8550&#8242; Distance: 4.0kms &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/10\/grey-creek-pass\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content":false,"footnotes":"","jetpack_publicize_message":"","jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled":true,"jetpack_social_post_already_shared":false,"jetpack_social_options":{"image_generator_settings":{"template":"highway","default_image_id":0,"enabled":false},"version":2}},"categories":[1],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-13374","post","type-post","status-publish","format-s